    <h1>Your week&#xAD;end din&#xAD;ing and en&#xAD;ter&#xAD;tain&#xAD;ment guide What to eat</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201225/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-25"><time>2020-12-25</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE STYLE WEEKEND</span>
        - <span role="byline">Eu&#xAD;nice Quek Food Cor&#xAD;re&#xAD;spon&#xAD;dent&#xD;&#xA;eu&#xAD;niceq@sph.com.sg</span>
    </section>

    <p>JA­PANESE-IN­SPIRED PIZ­ZAS PIZ­ZA­KAYA</p>
    <p>Takoy­aki (Ja­panese oc­to­pus balls) sit­ting pretty on a 10-inch hand-stretched pizza ($25.80, above) with a puffy, blis­tered crust – now that’s a pair­ing I ap­prove of.</p>
    <p>Then the gyudon ($25.80++) pizza ar­rives and it gets bet­ter. It is topped with Ja­panese-style braised beef, red gin­ger and on­sen egg – like what you would find in a beef rice bowl.</p>
    <p>Ex­pect th­ese creative Ja­panese-in­spired piz­zas at the new Piz­za­kaya – a joint ven­ture be­tween two of the largest food and bev­er­age play­ers in Sin­ga­pore.</p>
    <p>Brands un­der Mi­nor Food Sin­ga­pore in­clude ThaiEx­press, Xin Wang Hong Kong Cafe, and Poulet; while Ja­pan Foods Hold­ing has con­cepts such as Ajisen Ra­men, Menya Musashi and Fruit Par­adise.</p>
    <p>Other eye-catch­ing high­lights in­clude Ton­toro Ton­pei ($32.80++) pizza, with a gen­er­ous amount of sliced pork ton­toro (fatty pork neck) and cab­bage with a soft omelette draped over it; wagyu steak ($36.80) with onion rings; and ebi tem­pura mayo ($28.80) with tem­pura prawns and mashed potato.</p>
    <p>For a less savoury op­tion, go for the on­deh on­deh pizza</p>
    <p>($14.80++) with grated co­conut, co­conut ice cream, and lash­ings of gula me­laka.</p>
    <p>Purists may frown at th­ese com­bi­na­tions, but I’m all for us­ing the pizza dough as a blank can­vas.</p>
    <p>Each pizza comes with scis­sors for you to cut the slice size you want. The por­tions are best for shar­ing in a group or be pre­pared to take home left­overs.</p>
    <p>WHERE Piz­za­kaya, 01-157/158 VivoCity, 1 Har­bourfront Walk</p>
    <p>MRT Har­bourFront</p>
    <p>OPEN 11am to 10.30pm daily</p>
    <p>TEL 6224-9690</p>

